<br>
Allow me to state an alternate point of view...<br>
<br>
For some, EQ Romance &gt; RL Romance.  RL Romance takes work.  RL romance takes money.  RL Romance has consequences.<br>
<br>
EQ Romance...maybe you'd spend some plat, but cash is in infinite supply, unlike what you make in Real Life.<br>
<br>
EQ Romance...you don't have to meet the parents, the siblings, the aunts and uncles.  Just the friends, maybe a concerned guild leader.<br>
<br>
EQ Romance...if things get too heavy, too dramatic, too upsetting, you can turn it off.  It isn't as easy to do in Real Life.<br>
<br>
And for many, an EQ Romance allows them the freedom to share a small portion of themselves with someone else, that in Real Life they could not share because of the lack of anonymity.  If I'm a 6'7&quot; 400lb bald biker covered with tattoos and piercings, I can come on EQ and express my sensitive side without someone laughing at me.  If I'm a 4'2&quot; 400lb greasy-haired dependant with generic clothing and thick glasses, I can come on EQ and be that macho rich person I may wanna be.  I can approach 'women' without them automatically laughing at my girth or height or mullet.<br>
<br>
An EQ romance can let two mature people bond in a way that's purely emotional, free of the physical, and free of the social constraints that society might like to impose. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dididaryth>Didi D Aryth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Worshipping Tallonar since 3160</span><br>  Posts: 772<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/24/03 10:21:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=415.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: EQ ethics 1</span><hr size=1> Absolutely, that's why online romance is so attractive to many.  However, the question is assuming you DO have a RL romance.  No arguments here that EQ romance has good points.  But most people seem to be agreeing that IF you have a RL romance then that is &gt;&gt; EQ romance.<br>
